READ:
  If targets=0 is a near-zero fraction (<5%) and rows-per-team-week is
  consistently low (well under a realistic ~7-9 pass-catchers/team), the
  source likely omits zero-involvement players -- the receptions AUC is
  inflated by population truncation, not genuine predictability, and the
  model should NOT be wired live as-is.
  If targets=0 is well represented and rows-per-team-week looks like a
  real roster, the strong AUC is more likely genuine: reception rate is
  simply a more volume-driven, lower-variance signal than a single at-bat.
